name: Mathers Creek
description:
Introduction

The Haast River has Didymo. Be sure to avoid the river on the approach. Or you can wear different shoes and stash them and put on your canyon shoes when past the River section.

A really cool canyon with a nice variety of features. A worthwhile day, especially if adding on Imp if time allows.

Approach

Hike up Mather Creek until you get to the last rappel (arch). Check flow and then backtrack a few hundred meters until you see a good footpath that heads up the canyon right side. The path is well tracked for a while and then disappears. Enter the canyon just above the 500m topo line.

Descent

Exit

Simple and quick. 15 minutes
